    "Zhang et al. (2023) proposed E-NER, integrating evidential deep learning to quantify uncertainty and improve trustworthiness in predictions[35].",
    "The rise of large language models (LLMs) spurred novel approaches: Wang et al. (2023) developed GPT-NER[36], demonstrating LLMs' potential for direct entity recognition, while Ashok and Lipton (2023) introduced PromptNER[9], optimizing task-specific prompting strategies.Zhou et al.",
    "(2023) advanced UniversalNER[37], employing targeted distillation from LLMs to achieve robust performance in open-domain settings.",
